name: Wood Elves
text: When Wood Elves enters the battlefield, search your library for a Forest card and put that card onto the battlefield. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: Every branch a crossroads, every vine a swift steed.

name: Icatian Javelineers
text: Icatian Javelineers enters the battlefield with a javelin counter on it.\n{T}, Remove a javelin counter from Icatian Javelineers: Icatian Javelineers deals 1 damage to target creature or player.

name: Fiery Temper
text: Fiery Temper deals 3 damage to target creature or player.\nMadness {R} (If you discard this card, you may cast it for its madness cost instead of putting it into your graveyard.)

name: Boomerang
text: Return target permanent to its owner's hand.
flavor: "Returne from whence ye came..."\n—Edmund Spenser, The Faerie Queene

name: Calciderm
text: Shroud (This creature can't be the target of spells or abilities.)\nVanishing 4 (This permanent enters the battlefield with four time counters on it. At the beginning of your upkeep, remove a time counter from it. When the last is removed, sacrifice it.)

name: Reckless Wurm
text: Trample\nMadness {2}{R} (If you discard this card, you may cast it for its madness cost instead of putting it into your graveyard.)
flavor: Bred for battle in the Grand Coliseum, these wurms annihilated whole ecosystems when released into the wild.

name: Yixlid Jailer
text: Cards in graveyards lose all abilities.
flavor: He holds the keys to a tombful of incarcerated secrets.

name: Zoetic Cavern
text: {T}: Add {C} to your mana pool.\nMorph {2} (You may cast this card face down as a 2/2 creature for {3}. Turn it face up any time for its morph cost.)
flavor: Nothing lives within it, yet there is life.

name: Llanowar Elves
text: {T}: Add {G} to your mana pool.
flavor: Whenever the Llanowar elves gather the fruits of their forest, they leave one plant of each type untouched, considering that nature's portion.

name: Mogg Fanatic
text: Sacrifice Mogg Fanatic: Mogg Fanatic deals 1 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: "As if his chest had been a mortar, he burst his hot heart's shell upon it."\n—Herman Melville, Moby Dick

name: Mind Stone
text: {T}: Add {C} to your mana pool.\n{1}, {T}, Sacrifice Mind Stone: Draw a card.
flavor: "Except our own thoughts, there is nothing absolutely in our power."\n—Rene Descartes, Discourse on Method

name: Dauntless Dourbark
text: Dauntless Dourbark's power and toughness are each equal to the number of Forests you control plus the number of Treefolk you control.\nDauntless Dourbark has trample as long as you control another Treefolk.

name: Lava Axe
text: Lava Axe deals 5 damage to target player.

name: Cenn's Tactician
text: {W}, {T}: Put a +1/+1 counter on target Soldier creature.\nEach creature you control with a +1/+1 counter on it can block an additional creature.
flavor: "A well-trained force brings peace... which brings more time for training!"

name: Oona's Blackguard
text: Flying\nEach other Rogue creature you control enters the battlefield with an additional +1/+1 counter on it.\nWhenever a creature you control with a +1/+1 counter on it deals combat damage to a player, that player discards a card.

name: Gravedigger
text: When Gravedigger enters the battlefield, you may return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: A full coffin is like a full coffer-both are attractive to thieves.

name: Boggart Ram-Gang
text: Haste\nWither (This deals damage to creatures in the form of -1/-1 counters.)
flavor: "We’re going to need a bigger gate." —Bowen, Barrenton guardcaptain

name: Wilt-Leaf Cavaliers
text: Vigilance
flavor: Every elf in Shadowmoor is charged from birth with a terrible duty: to strike back against the ugliness and darkness, even though they are all around and seemingly without end.

name: Duergar Hedge-Mage
text: When Duergar Hedge-Mage enters the battlefield, if you control two or more Mountains, you may destroy target artifact.\nWhen Duergar Hedge-Mage enters the battlefield, if you control two or more Plains, you may destroy target enchantment.

name: Selkie Hedge-Mage
text: When Selkie Hedge-Mage enters the battlefield, if you control two or more Forests, you may gain 3 life.\nWhen Selkie Hedge-Mage enters the battlefield, if you control two or more Islands, you may return target tapped creature to its owner's hand.
